The paper deals with the compression of neural networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of transform coding and clustering also suggests a potential fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the compression of data over limited or expensive channels may also relate to information theory (cs.IT).
